---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="About Me – Cara Colgate, LICSW" currentPage="about">
  <div class="about-intro">
    <img
      src="/images/cara-headshot.jpg"
      alt="Cara Colgate, LICSW"
      class="headshot"
    />
    <div class="intro-text">
      <p>
        I am a clinical social worker with twenty years of experience supporting adults, children
        and families. It has been an honor to witness people grow and change. I have seen how the
        therapeutic process can instill hope, motivate change and lead to greater fulfillment.
      </p>
      <p>
        After graduating from Smith College School for Social Work, I completed a year-long
        fellowship at Children's Hospital, Boston in the adolescent and young adult clinic. Since
        then, I have worked with clients of all ages, from pre-school aged children to adults in
        hospice care. I have lived and worked in different countries, which has given me a deep
        appreciation for the cultural values that influence us.
      </p>
      <p>
        My training is rooted in psychodynamic theory and focuses on a strength-based approach.
        I have specialized training in cognitive behavioral therapy, grief and bereavement, sand
        tray therapy and parent-child psychotherapy. I also have a deep appreciation for 12-Step
        programs and recovery work.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <p class="full-width">
    Most recently, I have worked as a school counselor in both public and private schools
    supporting students, families and teachers. During my decade in schools, I have experienced
    how important collaboration with school teams and parents can be for children.
  </p>

  <p class="full-width license">
    I am licensed to practice in the state of Massachusetts (#121138).
  </p>

  <div class="education">
    <h2>Education and Training</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Master of Social Work, Smith College School for Social Work, 2003</li>
      <li>
        Post-Graduate Fellowship in Adolescent and Young Adult Medicine, Children's Hospital,
        Boston, 2003–04
        <ul>
          <li>Sand Tray Training Institute of New Mexico, Level 1, Corrales, NM 2005</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
      <li>Trust-Based Relational Interventions, Texas Christian University, July–August 2009</li>
      <li>
        Child Trauma Training Institute Certificate Program (CTI), 2009–2010
        <ul>
          <li>Child Life and Attention Skills Program, University of California in San Francisco, 2010–2011</li>
        </ul>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .about-intro {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr;
    gap: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    align-items: start;
  }

  .headshot {
    width: 100%;
    border-radius: 4px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.12);
  }

  .intro-text p {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
  }

  .full-width {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .license {
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--text-muted);
  }

  .education {
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
  }

  .education h2 {
    font-size: 1.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .education ul {
    max-width: 680px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .education li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    .about-intro {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }

    .headshot {
      max-width: 200px;
      margin: 0 auto;
    }
  }
</style>
